    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "Three new species of Magnolia (Magnoliaceae) endemic to the north-wet-arc in the Maya Highlands of Guatemala" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5814300>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5814290> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5814300>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Magnolia faustinomirandae. A-B. Flower at male phase. C. Isolated trees. D. Mature polyfollicles. E. Dehiscing fruit. F. Seeds, fruit after dehiscence. Photographs by E. Tribouillier." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5814300/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5814290>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Distribution of Magnoliaceae in Guatemala.Map A shows the full set of known Magnoliaceae localities for species occurring in Guatemala and extent rectangles for five closeup maps B–F; maps B, D, E represent Magnolia localities for species from section Magnolia, including close up to the North-Wet-Arc (B), to the zone of Huehuetenango and western Quiché (D); to Alta Verapaz, Baja Verapaz and eastern Quiché (E); map C is a closeup to the localities for species from section Talauma; map F is a closeup to the known confirmed localities of M. hondurensis and M. yoroconte." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5814290/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

